HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 924
By Salinas
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Clyde Victoria Staples
on the celebration of her 100th birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those citizens who are celebrating special occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Victoria Staples celebrates her 100th birthday on May 27, 2026, a
milestone to be commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Staples has lived a remarkable life, having experienced firsthand the
most eventful and productive years in American history and participated in civil rights meetings,
protests, and marches in Memphis in the late 1960s; and
WHEREAS, Clyde Staples worked as a licensed practical nurse for more than thirty-five
years, serving communities at John Gaston Hospital (now Regional One), William F. Bowld
Hospital, Tennessee Psychiatric Hospital and Institute, and the VA Medical Center; and
WHEREAS, she performed private-duty assignments and worked at area nursing
homes, and she also taught medical assistant and nursing assistant classes for Draughons
Junior College in the early 1980s; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Staples is the proud mother of nine children, grandmother of twenty-
five, great-grandmother of fifty, and great-great-grandmother of twenty; and
WHEREAS, a woman of abiding faith, Clyde Staples has enjoyed attending services and
worshiping at Parkway Gardens United Presbyterian Church, where she is a member of the
Presbyterian Women Organization; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Staples boldly follows the motto: "Every mouse to their own house,"
and she is proud to live independently in her own home and to cook and care for herself; and
HJR0924
012969
- 1 -

WHEREAS, she fills her days with her favorite pastimes, working jigsaw puzzles and
word searches, reading the Bible, watching Gospel videos and old movies, and talking on the
phone with friends and family who reap the benefits of her sage wisdom; and
WHEREAS, at the age of 100, Clyde Staples remains a blessing to all who know her and
is highly valued for her grace, compassion, and kindness; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly wish to grasp this golden
opportunity to specially recognize one of Tennessee's most outstanding citizens on this very
special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Clyde Victoria Staples on the
celebration of her 100th birthday and extend to her our best wishes for many happy returns of
the day.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
